728215f-a.text:
Woodhaven Boulevard (left not shown) east side, opposite Sixty-third Avenue, showing the J.S. Miller house of 1891. The house lies partially in both the Sixty-third Avenue and the Darmouth the Street lines, and will either be moved or demolished.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

728216f-a.text:
Woodhaven Boulevard, west side, south from Sixty-third Avenue (right foreground when constructed).  The prominently seen house was the property of the Geier or Geyer family from 1873 to 1909.  In the background is seen the farmhouse and outbuildings of Andrew Schmidt in 1909.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
